The President signed legislation to assist religious and ethnic groups targeted by ISIS for mass murder and genocide in Syria and Iraq. The bill also authorizes U.S. government efforts to bring perpetrators of these crimes to justice swiftly. The President thanked Vice President Pence, Administrator Mark Green, Ambassador Callista Gingrich, and Ambassador Sam Brownback for their support. He also recognized the members of Congress and religious leaders in attendance. The President emphasized the progress made in driving ISIS out of the region and expressed the administration's commitment to directing U.S. assistance toward persecuted communities. He also mentioned the importance of strong border security and the ongoing discussions with congressional leaders on the issue.